    "asOf": "2021-06-17",
    "date": "2021-07-23T17:53:42Z",
    "text": "Expanding Access to Graduate Education Act of 2021\n\nThis bill allows income-eligible graduate students who received Pell Grants during their undergraduate education to utilize their remaining Pell Grant eligibility toward their first graduate degree, subject to the existing 12-semester duration limit. Currently, Pell Grants are available only to undergraduate students."
